SIMPLE: exhilaration
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exhilaration
<hw>Ex*hil`a*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.,
<ets>exhilaratio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of enlivening
the spirits; the act of making glad or cheerful; a gladdening.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being enlivened or cheerful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Exhilaration</qex> hath some affinity with joy, though it be
a much lighter motion.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Animation; joyousness; gladness; cheerfulness;
gayety; hilarity; merriment; jollity.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exhort</ent>⟦br⟧
